<title>BELGIUM: RESEARCH ALERT - TESSENDERLO RATED 'BUY'.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT - TESSENDERLO RATED 'BUY'.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-08-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Brokerage Smeets' analyst Vincent Neefs said on Wednesday he maintained his 'buy' rating for Tessenderlo Chemie, the Belgian speciality chemicals firm.</p>
<p>In a report dated August 5 he said Tessenderlo was a 'buy' in view of</p>
<p>- its limited exposure to the economic cycle,</p>
<p>- the growth potential for fine chemicals and especially plastics processing, and</p>
<p>- its strong financial position and minimal debt.</p>
<p>The company would benefit from projected growth in the European chemical sector of 2.5 percent in 1997 and 1998; the largest contributors being organic products and plastics (+3.4 and +3.8 percent respectively).</p>
<p>    Estimates:   YEAR	  EPS	 DIV.</p>
<p>		     1996	  88	  33.3</p>
<p>		     1997	 111	  36.0</p>
<p>		     1998	 120	  38.7</p>
